news.title: Mumbai: Special CBI court cancels builder Satyen Tandon's bail
news.para: The court had then observed that though there was prima facie evidence against him, since he had deposited Rs 4 crore, it was a mitigating factor for granting bail.

news.title: Kochi: Immovable properties of Holy Faith Builders and Developers frozen
news.para: H2O Holy Faith was one among the four apartment complexes which were demolished in January 2020 for violation of coastal regulation zone rules.

news.title: Bombay HC slams builder for encroachment on playground plot
news.para: The PIL said that in 2019 the developer began construction for an SRA project in the neighbouring plot. In August 2021, excavation commenced on the playground reserved plot.

news.title: Gurugram: Shree Vardhman Flora's builder fails to clear dues, DHBVN snaps supply for two days
news.para: This comes after the discom snapped the power supply of the housing society on Monday owing to the pending electricity bills of over Rs 12 lakh.

news.title: Supertech twin towers - A lesson for both builders & officials: Noida Authority CEO
news.para: While declaring the towers illegal, the apex court had observed that the buildings could not have come up without the connivance of officials in the Noida Authority at that time.

news.title: Gurugram: Ardee City residents get refund over inadequate power infrastructure
news.para: The residents will get the refund as the developer has paid the required bank guarantee, allowing DHBVN to refund the development charges collected from the residents.

news.title: In relief to tenants, AAR allows tax credit on GST paid on upfront lease premium
news.para: Till now, tax authorities have been mostly disallowing input tax credit on upfront lease premium, arguing that this transaction is similar to immovable property and since no input tax credit is allowed in any real estate deal the same principal should apply to lease premiums, experts said.

news.title: GIC Housing Finance to raise up to Rs 2,500 crore via bonds
news.para: The housing financier will seek approval from its shareholders on the capital raise plan in the upcoming annual general meeting on September 23, 2022.

news.title: Final review complete, Supertech twin towers to be razed on schedule: Noida Authority CEO
news.para: The Noida Authority, which functions under the Uttar Pradesh government, is overseeing the demolition of the nearly 100-metre-tall structures in Sector 93A of the city.

news.title: HC asks AAI if it has relaxed height restriction for buildings near Navi Mumbai airport
news.para: On Thursday, Shenoy said while the situation in the Mumbai airport's vicinity was beyond repair, the authorities have now decided to lift the height restrictions for buildings near the proposed Navi Mumbai International Airport from 55.1 metres up to 160 metres.

news.title: Bring hammer down, Bombay HC tells BMC on buildings without water lines
news.para: “We can’t be doing this for every project in Bombay. You have to bring the hammer down. You can’t allow people to occupy such buildings,’’ said Justices Gautam Patel and Gauri Godse.

news.title: DMRC takes steps to prevent pollution due to Patna metro construction
news.para: To ensure that the soil and muck dug out during the construction work on underground and elevated section do not spill on the road, the DMRC has procured automatic 'Wheel Wash Facility' at all the construction sites.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Odyssa Homes & Commercials' MD held for cheating buyers of Rs 20 crore
news.para: Aurobinda Santara, MD of Odyssa Homes & Commercials Pvt Ltd, had floated an apartment project under the banner of Ganapati Homes near Kalinga Studio Chhak here in 2013.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Builder held for cheating two of Rs 4.4 crore after promising flats
news.para: According to the cops, two FIRs were filed against Saurin Panchal at Ellisbridge and Detection of Crime Branch (DCB) police stations on April 28 and May 14 respectively.

news.title: RLDA calls bid to lease 3.5 acres land in Dharmavaram for commercial development
news.para: RLDA will grant the land parcel for period of 45 years on lease. It has put the reserve price at Rs. 9.58 crore. RLDA vice-chairman Ved Prakash Dudeja said that the last date for submission of e-Bids is September, 13.
